### Fleet Management API - REST Client test suite
### Requires the "REST Client" VS Code extension (humao.rest-client)
### Make sure your server is running first: npm run dev

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api


### 1. Health check-ish: get all vehicles (should return [] on a fresh db)
GET {{baseUrl}}/vehicles


### 2. Create a vehicle
# @name createVehicle
POST {{baseUrl}}/vehicles
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "registrationNo": "GJ01AB1234",
  "model": "Tata Ace",
  "type": "Mini Truck",
  "maxLoadCapacityKg": 750,
  "odometer": 1200,
  "acquisitionCost": 550000
}

###
@vehicleId = {{createVehicle.response.body.id}}


### 3. Get all vehicles again (should now show the one you just created)
GET {{baseUrl}}/vehicles


### 4. Create a driver
# @name createDriver
POST {{baseUrl}}/drivers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rakesh Patel",
  "licenseNo": "GJ0520230001234",
  "category": "LMV",
  "licenseExpiry": "2028-01-01",
  "contactNo": "9876543210"
}

###
@driverId = {{createDriver.response.body.id}}


### 5. Dispatch a trip (uses the vehicle + driver created above)
# @name dispatchTrip
POST {{baseUrl}}/trips/dispatch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Ahmedabad",
  "destination": "Surat",
  "cargoWeightKg": 400,
  "plannedDistance": 265,
  "vehicleId": "{{vehicleId}}",
  "driverId": "{{driverId}}"
}

###
@tripId = {{dispatchTrip.response.body.id}}


### 6. Complete the trip
POST {{baseUrl}}/trips/{{tripId}}/complete
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "finalOdometer": 1465,
  "fuelConsumed": 25.5,
  "fuelCost": 2400
}


### 7. Financial analytics / KPIs
GET {{baseUrl}}/financials/analytics
